ight on the challenges faced by British ministers, civil servants, soldiers and policemen and the reasons why the conflict lasted so long. It will be a key text for researchers and students of both British and Northern Irish politics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aBritish politics.  aConflict.  aCounter-terrorism.  aLabour.  aNorthern Ireland.  aTerrorism.1 aAveyard, S.C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2016 eBook-Packagez978311128282440uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152610826540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526108265423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526108265/original  a978-3-11-128282-4  Manchester University Press 2016 eBook-Packageb2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles